**Financial Institution Which Accepts Deposits: A Bank's Unimpressive Existence**

This article details the often-overlooked, yet undeniably central, financial organization known as a bank, which inexplicably provides money under various conditions. For those who still manage to confuse it, see [Bank (disambiguation)](/Bank_(disambiguation)).

*   "Banks" and "Banker" are terms that, much like certain individuals, demand more attention than they perhaps deserve. For other uses, if you insist, see [Banks (disambiguation)](/Banks_(disambiguation)) and [Banker (disambiguation)](/Banker_(disambiguation)).

*   Part of a series on the baffling complexities of [financial services](/Financial_services) known as Banking.

The venerable [Bank of England](/Bank_of_England), an institution established in 1694, stands as a testament to humanity's enduring need to formalize the exchange of promises and coin.

